The paper deals with the implementation and performance evaluation of block diagonalization (BD) based precoding algorithms in the downlink of multi-user multiple-input multiple-output (MU-MIMO) systems, specifically in the framework of IEEE 802.11ac standard. This involves analyzing the sum-rate and bit-error-rate (BER) performance of the techniques and obtaining a computational complexity-wise as well as performance-wise optimal algorithm for the system. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the study of communication systems and their information processing capabilities. Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
